# Class: roadsigns:RoundaboutSign (Roundabout Sign)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment roadsigns:RoundaboutSign "Defined by the Vienna Convention as Sign D, 3. Notifies drivers they must follow the direction indicated by the arrows in a circular movement. 

Note: In Right-Hand Traffic (RHT) countries, circulation is anti-clockwise. Per Article 8, in Left-Hand Traffic (LHT) countries like Ireland, the symbol is mirrored to indicate clockwise circulation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label roadsigns:RoundaboutSign "Roundabout Sign"@en)
EquivalentClasses(roadsigns:RoundaboutSign ObjectIntersectionOf(roadsigns:RoundaboutSign ObjectSomeValuesFrom(roadsigns:hasSymbol roadsigns:RoundaboutSymbol)))
SubClassOf(roadsigns:RoundaboutSign roadsigns:DirectionMandatorySign)

