# Class: roadsigns:VColours (Strictly closed colour vocabulary of Vienna Convention Annex 1.)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment roadsigns:VColours "Colour meanings
        Black: Symbols and text
        Blue: Background of mandatory signs, information signs
        Green: Motorway information signs
        Orange: Temporary roadwork signs (some countries)
        Red: Borders of warning and prohibitory signs
        White: Background of prohibitory/warning signs
        Yellow: Alternative background for warning signs (some countries)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label roadsigns:VColours "Strictly closed colour vocabulary of Vienna Convention Annex 1."@en)
SubClassOf(roadsigns:VColours roadsigns:Colour)

# Class: roadsigns:VShape (Strictly closed shape vocabulary of Vienna Convention Annex 1.)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment roadsigns:VShape "Shape meanings
            Circle: Prohibitory and mandatory signs
            Inverted triangle: Yield / Give Way sign
            Octagon: STOP sign only
            Rectangle / Square: Information, guidance, and service signs
            Triangle: Warning signs (hazards ahead)

Not Vienna Standard shapes
            Diamond: 4-sided tilted square used in some countries for warning signs 
            Pentagon: 5-sided shape mainly used in the U.S. for school crossing signs"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label roadsigns:VShape "Strictly closed shape vocabulary of Vienna Convention Annex 1."@en)
SubClassOf(roadsigns:VShape roadsigns:Shape)

